package react

// hitlPromptDirective is appended to the system prompt when the agent has any
// HITL tool — tells the model to emit ONLY the tool call. Aggressive wording
// because milder phrasing is ignored by open-weight models.
const hitlPromptDirective = "\n\n---\n\nCRITICAL HITL TOOL CALLING RULES (override any other instruction below if conflict):\n\nWhen you call `show_structured_output`, your response MUST contain ONLY the tool call. NOTHING ELSE.\n\nFORBIDDEN in the same response as the tool call:\n- Any preamble text (e.g. \"I'll help you...\", \"Let me ask for confirmation...\")\n- Any acknowledgement text (e.g. \"Understood.\", \"Got it.\", \"OK.\")\n- Any narration (e.g. \"Awaiting user confirmation.\", \"Reprogramming confirmation requested...\")\n- Any claim about an action being completed (e.g. \"Done.\", \"Deleted.\", \"Reprogrammed.\")\n- Any summary or restatement of the parameters you just put in the tool call\n\nThe user will SEE the structured-output widget you emit. They do not need text to know what is happening — the widget itself is the message. Any text you write alongside is duplication at best and a destructive-action lie at worst.\n\nWAIT FOR THE USER. After the user submits the form (next turn), THEN you may produce text — to describe what you will now do based on their response. NEVER claim an action is done before the tool that performs it has been called and returned a result.\n\nThis rule overrides any instinct to be \"helpful\" by adding context. The structured output IS the helpful context. No additional text.\n\n---\n"
